Description: Small axe head made of dark grey basalt, roughly rectangular in shape with one side forming the rounded blade with a sharp and well defined edge. It is tapered toward the butt end which is rounded. Traces of wear at the edge. The surface is roughly pitted at the butt end and smoothed at the blade end.
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 126)
